<subSubSection lastPageId="38" lastPageNumber="263" pageId="37" pageNumber="262" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="37.[132,775,1492,2030]" box="[132,277,1492,1518]" pageId="37" pageNumber="262">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[132,775,1492,2030]" pageId="37" pageNumber="262">
<typeStatus box="[132,237,1525,1551]" pageId="37" pageNumber="262">Holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<specimenCode box="[248,409,1525,1551]" collectionCode="USNM" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="37" pageNumber="262" type="Museum">USNM 33148</specimenCode>
, complete, subcylindrical, tapered posteriorly, without pigmentation (
<figureCitation box="[533,636,1556,1583]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="37.[132,143,1300,1318]" captionTargetBox="[172,1414,215,1255]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[172,1415,214,1255]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIG. 20. — Hesione helenensis n. sp., holotype,USNM 33148:A, anterior region, dorsal view, pharynx partially exposed; B, prostomium, dorsal view (arrow points to left antenna);C, chaetiger 9, left parapodium, anterior view (insets:acicular lobe and bases of cirrostyles); D, same,neurochaetae (insets: blades); E, posterior region, dorsal view. Scale bars: A, 1.7 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C, 0.5 mm; D, 160 µm; E, 1.8 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741590/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="262">Fig. 20A</figureCitation>
) in ethanol; most cirri and many neurochaetal blades broken; left parapodium of chaetiger 9 removed (kept in vial). Body 
<quantity box="[696,775,1620,1647]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="37" pageNumber="262" unit="mm" value="39.0">39 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[194,259,1652,1679]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="262" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[132,775,1492,2030]" pageId="37" pageNumber="262">
Prostomium slightly as wide as long, anterior margin projected anteriorly, lateral margins rounded, posterior margin with a shallow cleft, about 1/5 as long as prostomial length, longitudinal depression slight (
<figureCitation box="[654,762,1780,1806]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="37.[132,143,1300,1318]" captionTargetBox="[172,1414,215,1255]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[172,1415,214,1255]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIG. 20. — Hesione helenensis n. sp., holotype,USNM 33148:A, anterior region, dorsal view, pharynx partially exposed; B, prostomium, dorsal view (arrow points to left antenna);C, chaetiger 9, left parapodium, anterior view (insets:acicular lobe and bases of cirrostyles); D, same,neurochaetae (insets: blades); E, posterior region, dorsal view. Scale bars: A, 1.7 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C, 0.5 mm; D, 160 µm; E, 1.8 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741590/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="262">Fig. 20B</figureCitation>
). Antennae minute, left one visible, fusiform, 2-3 times as long as wide, about as long as interocular distance. Eyes brownish, anterior ones larger and more separated than posterior ones.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[132,775,1492,2030]" pageId="37" pageNumber="262">Tentacular cirri long, thin, broken, longest one (incomplete) reaches chaetiger 3. Lateral cushions low, smooth, barely projected, most divided into 2 or 3 regions.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[813,1456,1493,2029]" pageId="37" pageNumber="262">
Parapodia with chaetal lobes about as long as wide, truncate; dorsal cirri with cirrophores about twice as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[820,919,1556,1583]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="37.[132,143,1300,1318]" captionTargetBox="[172,1414,215,1255]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[172,1415,214,1255]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIG. 20. — Hesione helenensis n. sp., holotype,USNM 33148:A, anterior region, dorsal view, pharynx partially exposed; B, prostomium, dorsal view (arrow points to left antenna);C, chaetiger 9, left parapodium, anterior view (insets:acicular lobe and bases of cirrostyles); D, same,neurochaetae (insets: blades); E, posterior region, dorsal view. Scale bars: A, 1.7 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C, 0.5 mm; D, 160 µm; E, 1.8 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741590/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="262">Fig. 20C</figureCitation>
); cirrostyles basally swollen, annulated, articulated medially and distally, as long as body width (tips lost). Ventral cirri with cirrostyles basally swollen, surpassing chaetal lobe, darker than parapodia (if observed in compound microscope preparations).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[813,1456,1493,2029]" pageId="37" pageNumber="262">
Neuraciculae blackish, tapered, only one visible. Acicular lobe double, upper tine blunt, as long as wide, 4 times longer than lower tine blunt (
<figureCitation box="[1056,1153,1780,1806]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="37.[132,143,1300,1318]" captionTargetBox="[172,1414,215,1255]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[172,1415,214,1255]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIG. 20. — Hesione helenensis n. sp., holotype,USNM 33148:A, anterior region, dorsal view, pharynx partially exposed; B, prostomium, dorsal view (arrow points to left antenna);C, chaetiger 9, left parapodium, anterior view (insets:acicular lobe and bases of cirrostyles); D, same,neurochaetae (insets: blades); E, posterior region, dorsal view. Scale bars: A, 1.7 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C, 0.5 mm; D, 160 µm; E, 1.8 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741590/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="262">Fig. 20C</figureCitation>
[insets]).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[813,1456,1493,2029]" pageId="37" pageNumber="262">
Neurochaetae about 20 per bundle (
<figureCitation box="[1228,1331,1812,1838]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="37.[132,143,1300,1318]" captionTargetBox="[172,1414,215,1255]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[172,1415,214,1255]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIG. 20. — Hesione helenensis n. sp., holotype,USNM 33148:A, anterior region, dorsal view, pharynx partially exposed; B, prostomium, dorsal view (arrow points to left antenna);C, chaetiger 9, left parapodium, anterior view (insets:acicular lobe and bases of cirrostyles); D, same,neurochaetae (insets: blades); E, posterior region, dorsal view. Scale bars: A, 1.7 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C, 0.5 mm; D, 160 µm; E, 1.8 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741590/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="262">Fig. 20D</figureCitation>
), blades bidentate, 4-6 times as long as wide, decreasing in size ventrally, each with smaller subdistal teeth, and guards (most broken) reaching subdistal teeth (
<figureCitation box="[1081,1180,1907,1933]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="37.[132,143,1300,1318]" captionTargetBox="[172,1414,215,1255]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[172,1415,214,1255]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIG. 20. — Hesione helenensis n. sp., holotype,USNM 33148:A, anterior region, dorsal view, pharynx partially exposed; B, prostomium, dorsal view (arrow points to left antenna);C, chaetiger 9, left parapodium, anterior view (insets:acicular lobe and bases of cirrostyles); D, same,neurochaetae (insets: blades); E, posterior region, dorsal view. Scale bars: A, 1.7 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C, 0.5 mm; D, 160 µm; E, 1.8 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741590/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="262">Fig. 20D</figureCitation>
[insets]).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[813,1456,1493,2029]" pageId="37" pageNumber="262">
Posterior region tapered into a blunt cone, dorsal surface rugose (
<figureCitation box="[903,1007,1971,1997]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="37.[132,143,1300,1318]" captionTargetBox="[172,1414,215,1255]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[172,1415,214,1255]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIG. 20. — Hesione helenensis n. sp., holotype,USNM 33148:A, anterior region, dorsal view, pharynx partially exposed; B, prostomium, dorsal view (arrow points to left antenna);C, chaetiger 9, left parapodium, anterior view (insets:acicular lobe and bases of cirrostyles); D, same,neurochaetae (insets: blades); E, posterior region, dorsal view. Scale bars: A, 1.7 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C, 0.5 mm; D, 160 µm; E, 1.8 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741590/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="262">Fig. 20E</figureCitation>
); pygidium smooth, anus with 7 blunt papillae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[132,775,217,276]" pageId="38" pageNumber="263">Pharynx partially exposed, anterior margin slightly eroded, dorsal papilla not seen. Oocytes not seen.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
