, and it could be confused with it. However, as indicated in the key below, 
<taxonomicName authority="Salazar-Vallejo, 2018" authorityName="Salazar-Vallejo" authorityYear="2018" box="[251,386,440,466]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Hesione" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="38" pageNumber="263" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="helenensis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[251,386,440,466]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="263">H. helenensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[392,450,441,467]" pageId="38" pageNumber="263" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Ehlers, 1887" authorityName="Ehlers" authorityYear="1887" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Hesione" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="38" pageNumber="263" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="praetexta">
